# Push to GitHub After Every Task

This project is linked to https://github.com/duckyquang/Donna.

After completing any user request that produces file changes:

1. Stage all relevant changes (never commit secrets like `.env` or credentials).
2. Create a commit with a clear message describing the change.
3. Push to `origin` on the current branch (`git push -u origin HEAD` if the branch has no upstream).

If there are no changes to commit, skip the commit/push step.

Do not ask for permission to push — pushing is expected after every task unless the user explicitly says otherwise.
